reviewText: Phrenetic, wacky, and over the top. If you are a stickler for quality of print, this may not be for you.

Anyone who did not grow up in Great Britain in the 1950s might find it hard to know the slightest thing about Old Mother Riley. My grandmother and I used to watch the shows on British TV and she would roar with laughter . . . I became a big fan then!
